Reference patch — hides the casper-wmi fan/pwm hwmon channels.

The WMI fan read (GET_HARDWAREINFO) hangs the kernel in an uninterruptible
D-state on some Excalibur BIOSes, which freezes `sensors` and the CPU-temp
reading. Making the hwmon channels invisible stops anything from triggering
that read. Fans are read from EC RAM by the excalibur-fand daemon instead.

install.sh applies this automatically via sed on /usr/src/casper-wmi-*/casper-wmi.c.
Equivalent manual change in casper_wmi_hwmon_is_visible():

	switch (type) {
	case hwmon_fan:
-		return 0444;	// read only
+		return 0;	// disabled: WMI fan read hangs; fans come from EC instead
	case hwmon_pwm:
-		return 0644;	// read and write
+		return 0;	// disabled
	default:
		return 0;
	}

Then rebuild:  sudo dkms build casper-wmi/<ver> --force && sudo dkms install casper-wmi/<ver> --force
